I just did some testing and it actually seems most of those issues with re-submitting events seems to be solved already.

Only `msg_showmode` seems to be re-submitted, but only once during redraw, so not an issue.

However, as soon as I have the cmdline open, I get spammed with `cmdline_show` events. Didn't yet look into it, but I assume that's because I force a redraw when the cmdline opens. Not an issue for Noice, since the cmdline ui will only update when the actual cmdline state changed.

Edit: and yes, noice honors `replace_last`

